# Blog ‚Äî data digest rules

## Purpose

- **Value:** Publish **data in a post-shaped layout** that answers a question city pages are not designed to answer (e.g. A vs B), using **the same numbers** as our guides. Do **not** copy long narrative blocks from city pages; **synthesize, tabulate, and link** instead.
- **Not:** Generic ‚ÄúAI travel‚Äù copy, first-person travel stories, or anything that overclaims visa, tax, or school outcomes.

## URLs & registry

- Routes: `/blog` (index), `/blog/[slug]`.
- Register every post in `lib/blog/registry.ts` with `getAllBlogPosts()` / `BLOG_POSTS`.
- Each post: `listTitle` (H1, no brand), `title` (SERP, ends with ` | FamiRelo`, ‚â§ 70 characters total; target **~65‚Äì70** with keywords), `metaDescription` (‚â§ **165** characters, **one or two complete sentences** ‚Äî write copy that already fits; `clipMetaDescription` is a last-resort trim with **no** `‚Ä¶`), `relatedCityIds` from `data/cities.json`, `publishedAt`, `tags`.

## SERP (align with `serp-metadata.mdc` and `serp-timeless.mdc`)

- Brand suffix: **`FamiRelo`**, not the full `Family Relocation Engine`, in the HTML `<title>` for blog.
- `buildPageMetadata` for canonical, OG, Twitter; **OG image** = first related city‚Äôs `resolveCityHeroImage` unless a post-specific asset is added later.
- `generateStaticParams` from `BLOG_POSTS`. Add new posts to `app/sitemap.ts` via the registry (already mapped).

## Layout & design

- **Layout:** `StickySearchHeader`, `Breadcrumb` (`Home` ‚Üí `Blog` ‚Üí current), `min-h-screen bg-[#F5EFE8]`, `max-w-3xl` article column ‚Äî same family as country/city pages.
- **Readability:** Short paragraphs, real `<h2>` / `<h3>`, tables with `overflow-x-auto`, avoid walls of text.
- **Byline / framing:** No dated byline on posts (no ‚Äúlast reviewed {month}‚Äù in SERP/OG) ‚Äî see `serp-timeless.mdc`. The article body can say figures match the city guides, without a review month in the byline.
- **No ‚Äúwhat this page is not‚Äù section in the middle** of a post ‚Äî stay useful. One short scope line in the intro or a single FAQ is enough for legal/careful phrasing.
- **FAQ:** end with `BlogFaqSection` (accordion, same pattern as city guide FAQ) ‚Äî not a flat `<dl>` list.
- **Footer block:** `You might also like` (or the same phrasing) with **internal** links to relevant city/country/destinations pages.
- **Premium:** Static digests are fine; the paid product can offer **interactivity, more dimensions, and saved comparisons** ‚Äî do not make every blog post an app substitute. Point to the guides for depth.

## Compare-tool CTA placement (mandatory ‚Äî pick one)

Every blog post must surface the personalized comparison tool. Pick the rule that matches the post type:

- **City-pair comparison post** (e.g. "Dubai vs Abu Dhabi", "Lisbon vs Porto"): use the shared `DataDigestCityComparisonArticle` (or `GenericPairComparisonArticle`, which delegates to it). It **automatically inserts `<BlogCompareCallout a={a} b={b} />`** above the FAQ ‚Äî both compared cities are pre-selected in the build flow via `?cities=a,b`. **Do not add a second CTA** ‚Äî the inline callout + the `/blog` index promo are enough.
- **Single-city deep dive, advice post, "best of" list, or any non-comparison post**: drop `<BlogComparePromo />` (from `@/components/blog/BlogComparePromo`) **once** between the conclusion and the "You might also like" footer. Generic copy, deep-links to `/compare`. **Do not** pre-select cities in this case ‚Äî there's no canonical pair.
- **`/blog` index page** (`app/blog/page.tsx`): keep `<BlogComparePromo />` near the top. Already in place ‚Äî do not duplicate.

Never use a modal, top fixed bar, or exit-intent popup for the compare CTA on the blog. The two components above are the only sanctioned placements.

## Structured data

- Use `lib/seo/buildBlogArticleJsonLd.ts`: `Article` + `BreadcrumbList` + optional `FAQPage` when the page shows matching Q&A.
- FAQs must be **on-page** and **aligned** with the FAQ schema; no FAQ stuffing that is not visible.

## New post checklist

- [ ] Add to `BLOG_POSTS` with all required fields
- [ ] Implement rendering in `app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx` (or a colocated content component) and `generateStaticParams` picks it up
- [ ] Title length / meta length spot-check
- [ ] `npm run build` ‚Äî static generation must succeed
- [ ] Sitemap includes `/blog` and `/blog/slug` (registry-driven)
